This Privacy Policy describes how Protect It ("We", "Our", "Us") collects, uses, and discloses your personal information when you use the app and informs you about your privacy rights and how the law protects you. By using Protect It, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Definitions
Company: Refers to Protect It and is used interchangeably with "We", "Us", or "Our" in this policy.
Device: Any device that can access Protect It, including computers, smartphones, or tablets.
Personal Data: Any information that can be used to identify or contact you.
Service: Refers to the Protect It application.
Service Provider: Third-party companies or individuals who process data on behalf of the Company to facilitate the Service or assist in analyzing how the Service is used.
Usage Data: Data automatically collected when you use the Service, including data from the app's infrastructure (e.g., ad IDs, device type).
Collecting and Using Your Personal Data
Types of Data Collected
We may collect the following types of personal data:
Personal Data: When using Protect It, we may ask you to provide personal information to identify or contact you, including but not limited to your email address and device-related data.
Usage Data: This data is automatically collected when you use Protect It. It includes information such as your device type, mobile operating system, IP address, unique device identifiers, and other diagnostic data.
Information Collected while Using the App: With your permission, we may collect additional information to provide certain features, such as location data or usage statistics.
Use of Your Personal Data
The collected personal data is used for the following purposes:
To provide and maintain the Service: We use your data to ensure the functionality and operation of the app and to monitor its usage.
To manage your requests: To respond to your inquiries, provide support, or handle your feedback.
For data analysis and improvements: Your data may be used to analyze usage trends, improve app performance, evaluate marketing campaigns, and enhance your experience with Protect It.
For legal and security purposes: We may use your data to ensure compliance with legal obligations and protect the security of our Service.
Your Rights and Options
Access and Correction: You may request access to your data and correct any inaccuracies.
Data Deletion: You can contact us to remove your personal information.
Opt-Out Options: You can disable personalized ads and request that your data not be shared.
Compliance with CCPA and VCDPA
Residents of California and Virginia have the following rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA):
Understand what data is collected and its purpose.
Request access to, deletion of, or correction of personal information.
Opt-out of data sharing and automated profiling.
Data Retention
We will retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. The retention period depends on the type of data and the purpose of collection. We also comply with legal requirements for data retention.
Data Disclosure
We do not share your information with unauthorized third parties. However, we may disclose your data:
To comply with legal obligations: If required by law or regulatory requests.
To protect our rights: To resolve security issues or protect the rights of the Company and its users.
Security Measures
We implement encryption and administrative controls to protect your data. However, please note that no system is completely immune to breaches, and we cannot guarantee absolute security of your information.
International Data Transfers
Your data may be processed in countries outside your country of residence. By using Protect It, you consent to these transfers, which may involve different privacy laws.
